added.title: Cool Uncles
added.description: The Titans take a trip to Wackadoodles, but Trigon makes Raven babysit her little brothers.

added.title: Butter Wall
added.description: When Beast Boy declares the Earth is a pancake, the Titans set sail to find out.

added.title: BBRAEBDAY
added.description: Raven's demon side has the same birthday as Beast Boy, so the Titans go to Azarath to celebrate her Sinister Sixteen.

added.title: The Cycle
added.description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais discover that Mr Wilson has been picking on their Dad for most of his life; ever since he humiliated Richard with a high school prank. The kids try to work Dad through it but when their efforts fail, they realize that getting back at Mr Wilson is the only way to break the cycle.

added.title: The Uncle
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are desperate to meet Ocho's famous uncle.

added.title: The Origins
added.description: When Mom and Dad struggle to keep hyperactive, toddler-aged Gumball from trashing the house and exhausting them, they decide to buy him a pet. It works, but there's a problem: every goldfish they get him is short-lived, and inevitably ends up being flushed down the toilet.

added.title: The Origins Part 2
added.description: Via the sewers, Darwin finds himself flushed out to sea. He is terrified but determined to make his way back to the Wattersons. However, a fish can't get very far on land so Darwin will have to do millions of years of evolution in a matter of hours if he's going to get home safe and sound.

added.title: The Finale
added.description: The Wattersons are surprised to discover that their past actions have consequences.

added.title: Dragon Pests
added.description: The Bears and Squatter Otter crash a couple's swanky pad while they're out of town.

added.title: No Land, All Air!
added.description: The Bears find themselves in a world of dog fighting planes and floating airships.

added.title: Jacob of the Creek
added.description: A terrible haircut forces Craig to go undercover at the Creek.

added.title: Return of the Honeysuckle Rangers
added.description: Craig discovers that the Honeysuckle Rangers have snuck into his side of the Creek to steal his most prized possession.

added.title: Kelsey the Elder
added.description: A spat between the Elders of the Creek leaves an opening in their tabletop role playing game, so Kelsey joins the campaign!

added.title: Dial B for Birder
added.description: Harold uncovers a secret plot that Chef's new parrot is hatching and tries to save his teacher only to discover that Sugar figured it out before him. Or did she?

added.title: A Hole Lot of Trouble
added.description: When rain derails an outside game of catch someone suggests they play it inside. This prompts Izzy to lead the group through her wildly imaginative worst case scenario. It's an adventure so scary that the kids many never play again.

added.title: A Tall Tale
added.description: After Owen's BBF, Noah, goes through a growth spurt, Owen fears losing his friend and takes drastic action.

added.title: Chews Wisely
added.description: When the floor ends up covered in gum on the day of a big bubble blowing contest, Sugar decides she might help herself win by helping her friends get stuck to the floor.

added.title: A Dingo Ate My Duncan
added.description: When all their classmates are replaced with well behaved Australian doppelgangers in a school exchange program, Lightning and Cody start getting suspicious.

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club 3: La Llorona
added.description: When Val sets out to get a little privacy in the woods, Vic is bent on pranking his unsuspecting brother,  that is, until Val goes missing.

added.title: In Your Own Skin
added.description: When Valentino is mocked for his lack of style, he's determined to get a designer hoodie to prove he has a sense of fashion, which turns out to be harder than it looks.

added.title: Ghosted
added.description: Vic makes a ghost friend but when she interferes with his shot at being part of the cool kids' Tlatchtli team, he must choose between the two.

added.title: Carmelita
added.description: Chata loans Xochi a car under the condition that Vic and Val can get rides when they need. However, the car becomes aggressive towards V&V and attacks!

added.title: Las Pesadillas
added.description: When Vic and Val experience a mysterious nightmare that turns deadly, they realize they must stop a sinister force from enchanting them to sleep forever.

added.title: The Audition
added.description: The Bears audition to be the next mascot for their favorite cereal. They get so caught up in the process that their competitiveness gets the best of them.

added.title: Baby Bears on a Plane
added.description: The Baby Bears have an adventure in the sky while aboard a plane to Sweden. But when the baby Bears are forced to sit in different sections of the plan, things get a bit haywire for everyone on board.

added.title: Icy Nights
added.description: Ice Bear rides his custom vacuum into the city. But when a gang of techies steal the vacuum, Ice Bear goes on a rescue mission that takes him through the underground world of the city.

added.title: Creature Mysteries
added.description: Ranger Tabes tells the Bears she's been investigating a mysterious creature. But when the Bears realize she's actually investigating their friend Charlie, they split up to ensure Charlie's safety.

added.title: Grizz Helps
added.description: When his brothers don't need his help for the day, Grizz leaves the cave to assist anyone he can throughout the city.

added.title: Panamanian Night Monkey
added.description: Apple and Onion must adopt unorthodox measures if they are to see this special animal at the zoo.

added.title: Broccoli
added.description: Some major construction is taking place on the roof of Apple and Onion's building and they can't get back home till it's finished.

added.title: Cousin's Day
added.description: It's Cousin's Day- another holiday the corporations made up to make more money and Apple and Onion are going to capitalise on it.

added.title: Nothing Can Stop Us
added.description: Hot Dog has the audition of his life but he is missing something crucial. Apple and Onion are tasked with bringing it to him and they are adamant that nothing will stand in their way.

added.title: Za
added.description: Pizza's Diner needs a makeover. Apple and Onion better get this right or Pizza is ruined.

added.title: Max to the Max
added.description: While Ben, Gwen, and Max hike to a waterfall, the Bugg Brothers are back with a plan to duplicate Diamondhead; but when their cloning ray gun fires on Max instead, multiplying him endlessly, Gwen and Ben must round up all the Maxes while also fighting off the Bugg Brothers.

added.title: Cutting Corners
added.description: Ben approaches Geezer Bob about doing a little yard work to earn spending money, but when Ben goes Upgrade to transform the lawnmower into a super fast mowing machine, he accidentally draws the ire of Bob's gnome-neighbors, the tiny, terrifyingly tenacious Billy-Bob Goblins.

added.title: Xingo
added.description: Ben is more interested in a marathon of his favorite cartoon show, "Xingo", but when Ben goes Upgrade to get a better signal, the titular Xingo leaps from his animated dimension to ours, bringing mad chaos with him!

added.title: Scared Silly
added.description: When the Rust Bucket runs out of gas on a foggy East Coast road, Ben, Gwen and Max are forced to stay at a hotel being menaced by Creepy Carl, a local folklore expert, who may actually be a ghost!

added.title: Need for Speed
added.description: Touring Yellowstone, Ben uncovers a plot by the fast & furious LaGrange to find treasure buried below the national park, but with a little help from Old Faithful, Overflow is able to douse LaGrange's dreams.

added.title: #WarriorAndTheJester
added.description: After accidentally destroying one of Babs' beloved, one-of-a-kind Batman keepsakes, Diana enlists the help of Harleen Quinzel in order to find a replacement in Gotham City.

added.title: #MotherKnowsBest
added.description: Hippolyta visits town and Diana is desperate to win her approval. But when Hippolyta unexpectedly takes a shine to Kara, Diana must curb her envy before they all get hurt.

added.title: #DetentionClub
added.description: Five socially disparate teens, Hal, Pam, Kara, Zee and Garth, find they have more in common than they thought after spending a Saturday in detention.

added.title: #SmallVictories
added.description: A malfunctioning device shrinks Karen into the Microverse, leaving technophobic Diana as her only hope.

added.title: #CruzControl
added.description: Working toward her dream of making her school a better place, Jessica runs for class president. However, when her opponent, the corrupt Oswald Cobblepot, pulls ahead in the race using less-than-honest means, Jessica finds herself compromising the integrity of her honest campaign to beat him!

added.title: Developing Dilemna
added.description: Frankie lets Elliott get a pet, which doesn't go down well with their new neighbor.

added.title: Inadvertant Inversion
added.description: As Elliott, Mo and Frankie all try something new at the Hive, they find their worlds are about to be turned upside down again.

added.title: Now We're Only Falling Apart
added.description: Pearl tells a story.

added.title: What's Your Problem?
added.description: Amethyst convinces Steven to take a day off for himself.

added.title: The Question
added.description: Steven shows some city slicker gems how the cowboys lived.

added.title: Mindful Education
added.description: Steven and Connie need to learn greater focus to take their training to the next level.

added.title: Mr. Greg
added.description: Steven, Greg and Pearl take a trip to Empire City to live the good life.

added.title: Broke His Crown
added.description: When Ice King's magic crown goes haywire, Marceline and Princess Bubblegum resort to extreme measures to help him.

added.title: Wheels
added.description: Kim Kil Whan is worried about his daughter's future and asks Jake for some parental advice.

added.title: Princess Cookie
added.description: Finn and Jake are called on to solve a Candy Kingdom hostage crisis when a rogue cookie takes over.

added.title: The Hard Easy
added.description: A delicate race of frog people employ Finn and Jake to help them deal with Prince Huge, an evil lizard creature who's ravaging the moss swamp.

added.title: Prisoners of Love
added.description: The boys try to cool off but get trapped by the Ice King.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: Unagami breaks into the real world and terrorizes Ninjago City while Jay, Zane and Pixal attempt to prevent disaster by reuniting Unagami with his creator, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: The ninja are invited to attend the birthday party of Princess Vania, in the distant Kingdom of Shintaro. They depart, bringing along Master Wu, unaware that he is feeling his age…

added.title: Into the Dark
added.description: When Cole investigates a mysterious visitor, the ninja aren't sure what to believe. Cole is frustrated with this lack of team support, until Princess Vania reveals a secret entrance that leads to an underground mine beneath Shintaro - where the city's dark secrets are held.

added.title: The Worst Rescue Ever
added.description: The ninja attempt to rescue Cole, but the bickering of his fellow prisoners, the Geckles and Munce, alerts the Skull Sorcerer, and soon the ninja are prisoners too.

added.title: The Two Blades
added.description: In order to escape the Skull Sorcerer's chain-gang, the ninja must convince the Munce and Geckles to put aside their distrust and work together… by promising them something they may not be able to deliver -- The Blades of Deliverance!

added.title: Classroom
added.description: Over the course of a single day in Ms. Baker's class, we see how Clarence and his classmates deal with their individual trials during the school day.

added.title: Dullance
added.description: Burned out from having so many adventures, Clarence struggles to sit around and do nothing.

added.title: Jeff's Secret
added.description: When Clarence discovers a new quirk about his friend, Jeff begs Clarence not to tell. Can Clarence resist the urge to expose Jeff's secret to the whole school?

added.title: Space Race
added.description: With Clarence distracted by the mysterious power of the moon, his class competes to build the highest-flying rocket. Will Sumo's homemade bucket of bolts beat Belson's store-bought rocket?

added.title: Plant Daddies
added.description: When Ms. Baker pairs up the kids to act as parents for a sprout, Sumo and Clarence learn all about good parenting. Jeff buys toys instead of fertilizer and Chelsea and Kimby get to know each other.

added.title: Party Pete
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby look for help when their awesome house party turns lame.

added.title: Brain Eraser
added.description: Benson gets demoted and has to work with Mordecai and Rigby.

added.title: This is My Jam
added.description: Rigby gets a terrible, terrible song stuck in his head and will go to any lengths to get it out.

added.title: Temp Check
added.description: Rigby hires a temp to do his work but gets jealous when the temp becomes tight with Mordecai.

added.title: Caffeinated Concert Tickets
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby make a deal with a Coffee Bean to help them stay awake to work major overtime to pay for concert tickets.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik/Their Fights
added.description: The Awesome Brawlers vs. Haavik: Dan and the Awesome brawlers have made their way up Haavik's tower as the final showdown between Haavik and the Awesome Brawlers begins./Their Fights: Haavik's Bakugan battle league rages on in an ultimate showdown between the Awesome Brawlers, vs Haavik and his destructive friends.

added.title: Haavik's Final Show/Miracle Planet
added.description: Haavik's Final Show: It's the final stage of Haavik's Bakugan Battle League: Dan and Drago Infinity vs. Haavik and his six-faction fusion Bakugan, Sabrus. Once again, the fate of two worlds, Earth and Vestoria rests in the hands of the Awesome Brawlers!/ Miracle Planet: The epic clash between Drago Infinty and Sabrus rages on. The winner of this clash of titans will decide the fate Earth and Vestroia.

added.title: Wiener Club
added.description: Puppycorn is determined to become the Hot Dog King and joins an underground hot dog eating contest called Weiner Club. Rick warns "you are what you eat," but Puppycorn doesn't listen and eats so many hot dogs he becomes the new champion of Weiner Club. Unfortunately he also literally turns into a hot dog, that the other club members reveal they are going to eat! Unikitty and the gang now must attack with vegetables and defeat the hot dog-eating baddies in order to save the giant hot-dog-shaped Puppycorn and turn him back to normal.

added.title: Trapped in the Tower
added.description: During a fun fireworks show, Unikitty and Master Frown become trapped in the horn of the Unikitty Castle when she catches Master Frown messing with her fireworks. Unikitty takes this as an opportunity to figure out why Master Frown is always such a Cranky McCrabby Face all the time, if only Master Frown would let his emotional guard down! She tries all kinds of tactics, a song, a dance, even a firework with a face drawn on it named "Professor Pow Pow, licensed therapist" Getting nowhere, Unikitty ends up raging out and setting the tower and all the fireworks alight. In desperation to not burn alive, Master Frown tells Unikitty a story about a younger Master Frown who was gifted a special lollipop but after a freak chain of events, was broken right before his eyes. Unikitty cries her eyes out and puts out the fires and then reveals it was her plan all along to get Master Frown to talk about his feelings!

added.title: Too Cool
added.description: Puppycorn needs a lesson in how to be cool. The gang is more than happy to teach him, until his coolness unexpectedly freezes the whole kingdom.

added.title: Unikitty and the Ice Pop Factory
added.description: An eccentric figure announces a contest to tour her marvelous ice pop factory, sending the gang on a frantic quest to find the winning popsicle stick.

added.title: The Very Best Candy
added.description: The gang can't decide which of their candy is the best, so they turn it sentient and have it fight to determine the winner.

added.title: Deep Space Vacation
added.description: When Gar lets KO and Enid take a vacation to outer  space, they get more than they bargained for.

added.title: Radical Rescue
added.description: Rad is forced to reconsider his identity when KO starts taking on some of his traits.

added.title: Dark Plaza
added.description: KO and the heroes of the Plaza fight to save Lakewood Plaza Turbo with everything on the line.

added.title: OK A.U.!
added.description: An evil warlock takes our heroes to a strange alternate universe.

added.title: Sibling Rivalry
added.description: When a new robot, Raymond, defeats the three heroes to steal the sign to Gar's, KO teams up with Darrell and Shannon to get it back.

added.title: The Truth Stinks
added.description: Badgerclops smells, but Mao Mao and Adorabat don't know how to tell him.

added.title: Trading Day
added.description: When they think each others' lives are easier, the heroes switch roles.

added.title: Head Chef
added.description: Mao Mao faces off with Badgerclops in a competition to determine whether cooking (and being a hero) is an art or a science.

added.title: Orangusnake Begins
added.description: Mao Mao goads Orangusnake and the Sky Pirates into becoming truly terrible villains worthy of a legendary hero such as himself.

added.title: Sugar Berry Fever
added.description: Mao Mao tries to hide his love of cobbler.

added.title: Ben 10,000
added.description: Ben gets sucked into the future by a grown up Gwen. His mission is to help the now all powerful and adult Ben 10,000 seemingly defeat the future versions of Dr. Animo and Vilgax. However, the real reason Ben has been brought to the future is to teach his adult self some humility and the fact he's lost touch with Max and has forgotten what's really important, family.

added.title: Merry Christmas
added.description: When the Rustbucket's A/C goes on the fritz in the middle of the desert, Ben, Max and Gwen take refuge at Holiday Village, an over the top Christmas theme park that seems to appear out of nowhere. The place is run by an evil entity known as Mr. Jingles, who takes Max prisoner because he believes Max is Santa! It's up to Ben and Gwen to free Max and break the spell Mr. Jingles has cast on Holiday Village, freeing others who've been trapped their for years and releasing the theme park.

added.title: Back with a Vengeance
added.description: Ben's feeling cocky with the watch. He's unlocked its secret, and now can become any alien he wants, whenever he wants. That's the good news. The bad news is, after finding one another in the depths of space, Kevin 11 and Vilgax have teamed up and have returned to earth to destroy Ben and get the Omnitrix.

added.title: Cough It Up
added.description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Universe vs. Tennyson
added.description: Ben gets dragged into intergalactic court by the other Celestialsapiens (Alien Xs) for recreating the universe (back in "So Long and Thanks for All the Smoothies").

added.title: Weapon XI Part 2
added.description: The Rooters have seemingly turned Kevin and the Amalgam kids against Ben. Can Rook and Gwen help him overcome the opposition and escape the Null Void?

added.title: Rook Tales
added.description: Rook's former teacher will preserve Revonnahgander traditions at any cost.

added.title: Uncle Baseball
added.description: A failing little league team on the brink of giving up gets help from Uncle Grandpa and some Major League Baseball players.

added.title: You Can't Handle the Tooth
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus must rescue Pizza Steve from the Tooth Fairy.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Movie
added.description: The gang attends the premiere of Majestico and Uncle Grandpa Boy, a movie about a little girl who wants to be a super hero.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa Land
added.description: Pizza Steve must find a way to sneak onto his own roller coaster at the newly opened Uncle Grandpa Land.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa at the Movies
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve cause a ruckus at the movies, Mr. Gus is forced to play the hero in order to save the day.

added.title: El Origen
added.description: La historia original de cómo Darwin terminó viviendo con los Watterson.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Jacob del Arroyo
added.description: Un terrible corte de cabello obliga a Craig a visitar el Arroyo de encubierto.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: El Regreso de los Guardabosques Madreselva
added.description: Craig descubre que los Guardabosques Madreselva se han infiltrado en su lado del Arroyo para robar su posesión más preciada.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Kelsey la Anciana
added.description: Una discusión entre los Ancianos del Arroyo deja un lugar vacante en su juego de rol de mesa, así que Kelsey se une a la campaña.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Juego Terminado
added.description: Unagami entra al mundo real y aterroriza a la ciudad de Ninjago mientras Jay, Zane y Pixal intentan evitar el desastre reuniendo a Unagami con Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: Los Ninjas están invitados a asistir a la fiesta de cumpleaños de la princesa Vania en la ciudad de Shintaro. Llevan al Maestro Wu que está deprimido.

added.title: En la Oscuridad
added.description: La princesa Vania revela una entrada secreta que conduce a una mina subterránea bajo Shintaro donde se guardan los oscuros secretos de la ciudad.

added.title: El Peor Rescate de la Historia
added.description: Los Ninjas intentan rescatar a Cole, pero las discusiones entre prisioneros alertan al Hechicero Calavera, y hace prisioneros a los otros Ninjas.

added.title: Las Dos Espadas
added.description: Para escapar de la prisión del Hechicero Calavera, los Ninjas debe convencer a los Munces y a Geckles de que dejen de discutir y trabajen juntos.

added.title: Hermanos Rivales
added.description: Cuando Raymond, un nuevo robot, derrota a los tres héroes para robarle el letrero a Gar, K.O. se alía a Darrell y a Shannon para recuperarlo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Juntos por Siempre
added.description: Connie tiene una visión muy clara de su futuro, y Steven quiere asegurarse de ser parte de esa visión.

added.title: El Futuro
added.description: Steven por fin está listo para avanzar.

added.title: La Verdad Apesta
added.description: Colosal huele mal, pero Mao Mao y Adorabat no saben cómo decírselo.

added.title: Dia de Intercambio
added.description: Cuando los héroes creen que la vida del otro es más sencilla, intercambian sus papeles.

added.title: Jefe de Cocina
added.description: Mao Mao se enfrenta a Colosal en una competencia para determinar si cocinar (y ser un héroe) es un arte o una ciencia.

added.title: El Comienzo de Cobrangutan
added.description: Mao Mao incita a Cobrangután y a los Piratas del Cielo a convertirse en villanos verdaderamente malvados, dignos de un héroe legendario como él.

added.title: Fiebre de la Baya de Azúcar
added.description: Mao Mao intenta ocultar su amor por el pastel de fruta.

added.title: Max Al Maximo
added.description: Mientras Ben, Gwen y Max van de excursión a una cascada, los Hermanos Bugg regresan con el plan de duplicar a Diamante. Pero cuando su arma láser clonadora le dispara a Max por error-y lo multiplica infinitamente-, Gwen y Ben deben juntar a todos los Maxes y ahuyentar a los Hermanos Bugg a la vez.

added.title: Cortando Camino
added.description: Ben habla con Geezer Bob para hacer alguna tarea de jardín y así ganar un poco de dinero, pero cuando Ben se transforma en Upgrade para convertir la podadora de césped en una cortadora súper rápida, por accidente despierta la ira de los vecinos gnomos de Bob: los diminutos y aterradoramente obstinados duendes de Billy Bob.

added.title: Xingo
added.description: Ben está muy interesado en una maratón de Spazz, su dibujo animado favorito, pero cuando se transforma en Upgrade para mejorar la señal de televisión, el protagonista de Spazz salta de su dimensión animada hacia la nuestra...iy trae consigo un caos demente!

added.title: Muerto De Miedo
added.description: Cuando la Chatarra se queda sin gasolina en una carretera brumosa de la Costa Este, Ben, Gwen y Max se ven obligados a pasar la noche en un hotel amenazado por Creepy Carl, iun experto en folclore de la zona que podría ser un fantasma verdadero!

added.title: Necesidad De Velocidad
added.description: De paseo por Yellowstone, Ben descubre el plan del rápido y furioso LaGrange para encontrar un tesoro enterrado bajo el parque nacional. Pero con una ayudita del géiser Viejo Fiel, Overflow logra empapar los sueños de LaGrange.

removed.title: #WorkingStiff
removed.description: After Babs hooks Karen up with a job at the Burrito Bucket the two heroes encounter a new villain, the scourge of the fast-food underworld, the Condiment King!

removed.title: The Curse
removed.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

removed.title: TP2: Judgement Bidet
removed.description: When the city experiences a toilet paper shortage Beth and Harold investigate and discover it's their old rival Sewer Mike who is the mastermind behind it all.

removed.title: #Powerless
removed.description: Supergirl loses her powers and, with the help of BumbleBee, must rely on her street smarts to save Garth from vengeful Toyman.

removed.title: Sheep Bears
removed.description: The Bears get jobs as sheep herders on an idyllic farm.

removed.title: Everything's Fine
removed.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

removed.title: Ninjago Confidential
removed.description: Back in Ninjago City, Zane and Pixal hit the mean streets to track down Milton Dyer, only to discover that things are not what they seem.

removed.title: Ninjago Confidencial
removed.description: De vuelta en la ciudad de Ninjago, Zane y Pixal salen a las calles para encontrar a Milton Dyer, y descubren que las cosas no son lo que parecen…

removed.title: Weapon of Choice
removed.description: Worried that his sword is a glorified consolation prize, Mao Mao sets out to prove the worth of his weapon.

removed.title: Bobo Chan
removed.description: Badgerclops adopts an abandoned monster, but some things are better left in the wild.

removed.title: #TheMinus
removed.description: Diana receives her first ever A minus and becomes convinced that she needs to work harder, however, in order to do so, she resorts to rather drastic measures.

removed.title: WaterHose-Five
removed.description: The hottest day of the year and a broke air conditioner leads to a water battle of epic proportions to determine who controls the garden hose.

removed.title: Pequeno
removed.description: El legendario, gigantesco y crítico padre de Mao Mao visita a su hijo en su nuevo trabajo como sheriff.

removed.title: Memory Mayhem
removed.description: Frankie tries to discover more about the mysterious rock that bought them to their new home, with the help of an entity called The Head.

removed.title: Small
removed.description: Mao Mao's legendary, gigantic and critical father visits his son at his new job as sheriff.

removed.title: Say Hello to my Little Friends
removed.description: After telling the kids he will not miss them over the long weekend Chef locks himself into the school and finds out he was very, very wrong.

removed.title: I Am My Monster
removed.description: Everything is not fine.

removed.title: Meet Tanya Keys
removed.description: When bounty hunter Tanya Keys comes to town for Badgerclops, it's up to Mao Mao and Adorabat to save their friend -- even if he's been on the wrong side of the law.

removed.title: The Prodigal Father
removed.description: Zane, kidnapped by the Mechanic, faces Unagami. Master Wu fights to free Zane, while Pixal questions Milton Dyer for information on how to shut down Prime Empire.

removed.title: Soy Mi Monstruo
removed.description: No todo está bien.

removed.title: Charlene Mania
removed.description: When Vic attempts to have the perfect day off, the town's sudden obsession for Charlene gets in his way.

removed.title: Stop, Drop and Side Scroll
removed.description: Our ninja barely have time to mourn the loss of their fallen ninja friends before being thrust into the madness of Terra Domina where Lloyd will have to face an old adversary from his past.

removed.title: The Speedway Five-Billion
removed.description: Unagami's soldiers, the Red Visors, finally discover the secret location of Scott's garage and attack the ninja, who manage to escape with the help of Racer Seven, and enter the spectacular Speedway Five Billion.

removed.title: Memories of Bobby
removed.description: When a pillar of the Creek community leaves, our trio mourns their loss by remembering the good times.

removed.title: #MultipliciZee
removed.description: Zee magically duplicates herself so she can shirk work and watch TV. Things get out of hand when her copies start to make copies of themselves!

removed.title: Arma de Eleccion
removed.description: Preocupado de que su espada sea un premio consuelo con pretensiones, Mao Mao decide salir a demostrar el valor de su arma.

removed.title: #AcceptNoSubstitute
